  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Cardiac output, the amount of blood pumped by the heart in one minute, will be measured in
      adults undergoing surgery involving cardiopulmonary bypass. Cardiac output will be measured
      before and after cardiopulmonary bypass using a device that employs ultrasound dilution
      technology. The ultrasound dilution cardiac output measurements will be validated or compared
      with cardiac output measurements made using thermodilution, which is the current &quot;gold
      standard.&quot;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
